Prototyping Neural Network algorithm visualization

`simulation.json`
```javascript
{
	"polygroup": [{
		"5": [ 					// timestep this node was activated
      							// each tuple describes incoming activations
			[2, 3],				// [node index, timestep when this node fired]
			[1, 4]				// 
		]
	}, {}, {					
  									// this node (index 2) fired at times 2 and 6
		"2": [
			[0, 2],
			[2, 2]
		],
		"6": [
			[0, 6],
			[1, 4]
		]
	}],
	"init": [1, 3, 1],
	"numTimeSteps": 6,
	"network": [
		[0, 2, 3],
		[1, 4, 2],
		[1, 3, 1]
	]
}
```

NOTES
  // when a node fires, what would be super cool is in the connection
  // between two nodes, that node can increase or decrease in size, can
  // flash different color whether plasticity is increasing or decreasing


Also using [@sxywu's trick](http://blockbuilder.org/sxywu/9354026) of adding links as invisible nodes and centering them between source and target, this keeps the graph from forming straight lines in some configurations.

Using [@erkal's polygon links](http://blockbuilder.org/erkal/9746652).

